            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650985668784-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650985668784-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Soak the <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking) and take<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> butter alternative</strong> out of the fridge and set aside to warm up</p><p>Combine 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp] </span><strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) in a small bowl – this is your <strong>vinegar mop</strong></p><p>Tip: In Southern BBQ a mop sauce is used to baste barbecued meats to infuse the meat (or meat-free!) with flavour while it cooks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650985673567-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650985673567-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
